caption: Consistently delicious rolls (drunken, spicy shrimp, joyride are awesome), super fast delivery. Quickly has become my go-to sushi takeout spot.

Ordered delivery and everything looked great, presentation was on point and flavors were good. Only gripe would be the fish portions. The rainbow roll was basically all rice with a sliver of fish on top, it was disappointing. The other roll was tasty, just a lot of rice!  Maybe an off night so want to give the benefit of the doubt...

Man, the sushi was good here. I asked if they could make the miso spicy and they did! The chefs special was the Red Spider and it was the delicious. All around great. The chef makes good sushi. And the server was great too!

Overall really great sushi! Godzilla roll and Dragonfly rolls had some amazing flavors. The Spider roll wasn’t as crunchy as we’ve had at other places and it was a little bland. The Crazy roll had a nice spicy kick to the end of the bite that made it worth it too.  And another nice touch is that they wrote the names on the box!! I LOVE this extra piece of thoughtfulness! Will definitely be back!
Ordered with my three roommates and we all loved it. I would recommend my friends to come eat here. Can't wait till we can all dine in together!
Unbeatable prices for quality! Decent sizes, fresh fish, well pair ingredients. The rolls are all perfectly done classics with some really tasty specialty rolls.

We try and support local one time a week and this week we noticed this opened so we gave it a shot.  We tried 4 different rolls, two specialty and two regular.  They were fresh and flavorful!  Simple menu, great prices and delicious.  Do yourself a favor and try it!  You won’t regret it.
